00:00:45.460 --> 00:00:50.960
Pretty much any company as long as they buy or set up a phone or internet service provider can avoid

00:00:51.280 --> 00:00:56.840
protection actions from the FTC. and in this case if that ruling is not repealed the FCC will shift

00:00:56.900 --> 00:01:00.260
responsibility for handling net neutrality complaints to the FTC.

00:01:00.480 --> 00:01:04.199
What that means is they will have limited options for fighting for you then.

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:08.620
This makes it much easier for people and sites to be abused by big corporations

00:01:09.120 --> 00:01:12.540
I know what you're thinking. "Oh come on that won't happen." It already has!

